        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-17T14:15:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If at the end of the flush, then yes, that difference represents all the excess space we needn\u0027t have allocated.\n\nThere may possibly be other wasted space from alignment padding, or allocations that were released but not recoverable (because they weren\u0027t at the end). In these cases, those bytes are still counted as space in use and we can\u0027t detect that type of waste.",
      "parentUuid": "78ff8e6d_631f49e7",
      "revId": "bf5984699f82929125f744af1fed887f4f123051",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
